<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9756&amp;p=107018#p107018"><![CDATA[
<ul><li>The BBCode element for ordered and unordered lists is called &quot;list&quot;</li><li>The list element is transformed into an HTML ol or ul element based on its attribute being present or absent</li><li>Each item in the list is inside a &quot;*&quot; element</li><li>Like HTML (and unlike XHTML), BBCode has elements whose closing tag is optional in certain circumstances because the element can't directly contain itself</li><li>For example, the closing tag for the * element is optional</li><li>To see the BBCode source for this post, click the quote button</li></ul><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Jan 29, 2013 5:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
