<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9756&amp;p=106994#p106994"><![CDATA[
BBCode lists are kinda crappy... This works fine:<br /><br /><ul>Random list:<br /><li> First item;</li><li> Second item;</li></ul><br />But when you're replying and quoting individual items in the list you get this:<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />[*] First item;<br /></div><br />...unless you add a new list tag for each quote. Even though that is in fact the expected behavior, it's still annoying, so I just tend to avoid lists.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Jan 28, 2013 7:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
